{
  "text": "For example, the first passage flow of node 4(G 4 ) can be calculated as, Actually, each term of Equation B.3 is the first passage flow from node j to i, that is the number of particles that have visited j (in whatever time) and finally arrive at i in the first time along all possible flow pathways. By dividing by the term u ii to derive first passage flow one avoids duplicate counting the particles who have visited i [CITATION_1] .",
